extended_tweet.full_text:
Shinnecock Hills US Open Tour
No. 16 - 616yds - Par-5 (1 of 2)
Shinnecock, the eponymous 16th, begins our home stretch. The second of Shinny’s two par-5s, this hole has a new tee which adds 76 yards in length, but downwind, players can still have a go at this green.
#LGshinnytour https://t.co/8auMzhiG4n

...and watch both those guys go driver, hybrid into the bunker.  Good to see a new tee that hopefully makes 16 a 3 shotter again.  Into the breeze on Sunday afternoon, eventual winner will have to execute 3 great shots #shinnecock #usopen (2/2) https://t.co/rO8Klqxs6w

Shinnecock Hills US Open Tour
No. 17 - 180yds - Par-3
A devilishly tricky one-shotter frequently buffeted by confounding crosswinds and featuring a pushed up green with no background to help with judging distance, the 17th may well determine this week’s winner.
#LGshinnytour https://t.co/zR7zouyvMI

Stand on 17 and the course tells you “you are just an amateur”.  A prevailing left to right breeze means you need to hold a draw on this stout par 3.  Pavin and Goosen made stellar 3’s en route to victory.  Doubt we see a birdie for the last hour of #USOpen #Shinnecock https://t.co/EDqjQXB0ny
